    "chemicalDescription": [
      "Tripeptide-46 Hexapeptide-40 Oligopeptide-96 Oligopeptide-91 Tetrapeptide-38 rh-Polypeptide-9 is a single chain synthetic fusion peptide, produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the gene from Tripeptide-46, Hexapeptide-40, Oligopeptide-96, Oligopeptide-91, Tetrapeptide-38 and rh-Polypeptide-9. The fused peptide contains 212 amino acids and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
